    "In a direct calculation, such as ours, which avoids the GPD route to gravitational form factors, there is no D-term ambiguity in the analysis of θ 1 (t) [82].",
    "It is notable, therefore, that the value θ 1 (t = 0) = 0.97 -see Table 2, matches the estimate obtained using chiral effective field theory [79].",
    "The predictions for the θ π 2 and F π radii are consistent with recent extractions [37,81], confirming thereby that the distribution of mass within the pion is more compact than the distribution of charge: r θ 2 π /r F π = 0.74.",
